<DIV1>
<PB REF="255">
<HEAD>A
SPECIMEN
OF THE
ORIGINAL
OF
TEMORA.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">BOOK SEVENTH.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="advertisement">
<PB REF="256">
<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P>IT is thought proper to give a &s;pecimen of the original Galic,
for the &s;atisfaction of tho&s;e who doubt the authenticity of O&s;&s;ian's
poems. The &s;eventh book of TEMORA is fixed on, for that pur|po&s;e,
not from any other &s;uperior merit, than the variety of its
ver&s;ification. To print any part of the former collection was
unnece&s;&s;ary, as a copy of the originals lay, for many months, in
the book&s;eller's hands, for the in&s;pection of the curious. Tho'
the erroneous orthography of the bards is departed from, in ma|ny
in&s;tances, in the following &s;pecimen, yet &s;everal quie&s;cent con|&s;onants
are retained, to &s;hew the derivation of the words. This
circum&s;tance may give an uncouth appearance to the language,
in the eyes of tho&s;e who are &s;trangers to its harmony. They
ought, however, to con&s;ider, that a language is put to the &s;e|vere&s;t
te&s;t, when it is &s;tripped of its own proper characters; e&s;|pecially,
when the power of <HI>one</HI> of them requires, &s;ometimes,
a combination of two or three Roman letters to expre&s;s it.</P>
<DIV3>
<PB N="227" REF="257">
<HEAD>A
SPECIMEN
OF THE
ORIGINAL
OF
TEMORA.</HEAD>
<DIV4 TYPE="book">
<HEAD>BOOK SEVENTH.</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>O Linna doir-choille na <HI>Leigo,</HI></L>
<L>Air uair, eri' ceo taobh-gh&oacute;rm nan t&oacute;n;</L>
<L>Nuair dhunas dor&s;a na h'oicha</L>
<L>Air iulluir-&s;huil greina nan &s;peur.</L>
<L>Tomhail, mo <HI>Lara</HI> nan &s;ruth,</L>
<L>Thaomas du'-nial, as doricha cruaim:</L>
<L>Mar ghlas-&s;cia', roi taoma nan nial,</L>
<L>Snamh &s;eachad, ta Gellach na h'oicha.</L>
<L><PB N="228" REF="258">
Le &s;o edi' tai&s;in o-&s;hean</L>
<L>An dlu'-ghleus, a mea&s;c na gaoith,</L>
<L>'S iad leamnach, o o&s;na gu o&s;na,</L>
<L>Air du'-aghai' oicha nan &s;ian.</L>
<L>An taobh oitaig, gu palin nan &s;eoid,</L>
<L>Taomas iad ce&auml;ch nan &s;peur,</L>
<L>Gorm-thalla do thannais nach b&eacute;o,</L>
<L>Gu &aacute;m eri' f&oacute;n marbh-r&aacute;n nan teud.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>TA torman, a machair nan cr&aacute;n</L>
<L>Se <HI>Conar</HI> ri <HI>Erin</HI> at' &aacute;n,</L>
<L>A taoma' ceo-tanais gu dlu'</L>
<L>Air <HI>Faolan</HI> aig <HI>Lubhair</HI> nan &s;ru'</L>
<L>Muladach, &s;uigha fo bhr&oacute;n,</L>
<L>Dh'aom an tais an ceach an loin.</L>
<L>Thaom o&s;na, e&s;&s;in an fein,</L>
<L>Ach phil an cruth aluin, gu di&auml;n</L>
<L>Ph&iacute;l &eacute; le chrom-&s;healla m&aacute;l</L>
<L>Le cheo-leatain, mar &s;huibhal nan &s;ian.</L>
<L>'S doilleir &s;o!</L>
<L>Ata na &s;loigh na n&s;uain, &s;an &aacute;m,</L>
<L>An tru&s;can cear na h'oicha:</L>
<L>Dh' il&s;ich teina an ri, gu ard,</L>
<L>Dh' aom &eacute; na aonar, air &s;cia'.</L>
<L><PB N="229" REF="259">
Thuit cod&aacute;l, mo &s;huillin a ghai&s;cich,</L>
<L>Thanic guth <HI>Fhaolan,</HI> na chluais.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>AN codal &s;o, don' fhear-pho&s;da aig <HI>Clatho?</HI></L>
<L>Am bail coni do m' athair, an &s;uain?</L>
<L>Am bail cuina, 's mi 'ntru&s;can nan nial?</L>
<L>'S mi m' aonar an &aacute;m na h'oicha?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CUR &s;on ta &uacute;, a m' a&s;lin fein?</L>
<L>Thubhart <HI>Fion-ghael,</HI> 's &eacute;'g eri grad.</L>
<L>An dith-chuin, d'om&s;e, mo mhac,</L>
<L>Na &s;hiubhal teina air Rethlan nan laoich?</L>
<L>Ni mar&s;in, air anam an ri,</L>
<L>Thig gniomh &s;eoid aluin na ncruai'-bheum.</L>
<L>Ni ndeallan iad&s;e, a theichas an dubhra</L>
<L>Na h'oicha, 'snach fh&aacute;g a lorg.</L>
<L>'S cuina liom <HI>Faolan</HI> na &s;huain:</L>
<L>'Ta m'anam aig eri' borb.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>GHLUAIS an ri, le &s;leagh, gu grad,</L>
<L>Bhuail e n&s;cia' as fuaimnach cop,</L>
<L>An &s;cia' a dh' aom &s;a n'oicha ard,</L>
<L>Bal-mo&s;gla' do ch&aacute;th nan l&oacute;t.</L>
<L>Air aomagh du' nan &s;liabh,</L>
<L><PB N="230" REF="260">
Air gaoith, theich treud nan tais:</L>
<L>O ghleanan cear nan ioma l&uacute;p,</L>
<L>'Mho&s;guil guth a bhais.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>BHUAIL &eacute; 'n &s;cia, an darra cuairt,</L>
<L>Ghluais coga, an a&s;lin an t'&s;hluaigh:</L>
<L>Bhith comh-&s;ri nan l&aacute;n glas&mdash;</L>
<L>A dcalra' air anam nan &s;eoid,</L>
<L>Ciean-fheona a truita' gu cath,</L>
<L>Slua' a teicha,&mdash;gniomh bu chruai',</L>
<L>Leth-dhoilleir, an deallan na &s;talin.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NUAIR dh' erich, an darra fuaim,</L>
<L>Leum feigh, o ch&oacute;s nan c&aacute;rn</L>
<L>Chluinte a &s;creadan &s;c&eacute;', &s;a n' fha&s;ich&mdash;</L>
<L>Gach Ean, air o&s;na fein.</L>
<L>Leth-erich &s;iol <HI>Albin</HI> nam buaigh</L>
<L>Thog iad &s;uas gach &s;leagh, bu ghlas:</L>
<L>Ach ph&iacute;l &s;achir, air an l' &s;hluaigh,</L>
<L>Se bh' &aacute;n &s;cia' <HI>Mhorbhein</HI> na mfras.</L>
<L>Ph&iacute;l codal, air &s;uilin na mfear:</L>
<L>Bu dorcha, tr&oacute;m a nglean.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="231" REF="261">
<L>NI mo chodal, duit&s;e &eacute;, &s;a nuair,</L>
<L>Nion &s;huil-gh&oacute;rm <HI>Chonmor</HI> na mbuaigh,&mdash;</L>
<L>Chuala <HI>Suil-mhalla</HI> an fhuaim</L>
<L>Dh' erich i, fa n' oicha, le cruaim:</L>
<L>Ta ceum gu ri <HI>Atha</HI> na ncolg:</L>
<L>Ni mo&s;guil cunart anam borb.</L>
<L>Tr&oacute;m a &s;h&eacute;&s;i,&mdash;a &s;uilin &s;ios.</L>
<L>Ta 'n&s;peur an lo&s;ga nan reul.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CHUALAS l&eacute; &s;ciath na nc&ograve;p.</L>
<L>Ghluais;&mdash;ghrad &s;h&eacute;s an Oi:&mdash;</L>
<L>Dh' erich a gu'&mdash;ach dh' aom &eacute; &s;ios.&mdash;</L>
<L>Chuinic &iacute;s &eacute;, na &s;talin chruai,</L>
<L>A dealra ri lo&s;ga nan reul:</L>
<L>Chuinic is &eacute;, na leatan thr&oacute;m.</L>
<L>Aig eri ri o&s;na nan &s;peur.</L>
<L>Thionta i ceamna, le fiamh,</L>
<L>Cur&s;on dhui&s;gim&s;e Ri <HI>Erin</HI> na m <HI>B&oacute;lg,</HI></L>
<L>Ni n' a&s;lin do chodal u-fein,</L>
<L>A nion <HI>Inis-uina</HI> na nc&oacute;lg.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Gu garg a mho&s;gul an torman;</L>
<L>On' oi thuit a cean-bh&eacute;rt &s;ios:</L>
<L>TA mforum, air carric nan &s;ruth.</L>
<L><PB N="232" REF="262">
Plao&s;ga, o a&s;lin na h'oicha,</L>
<L>Ghluais <HI>Cathmor</HI> fa' chr&aacute;n fein.</L>
<L>Chuinic &eacute; n' Oi bu tla,</L>
<L>Air carric <HI>Lubhair</HI> nan &s;liabh:</L>
<L>Dearg re&ubreve;l, a &s;ealla &s;ios,&mdash;</L>
<L>Mea&s;c &s;iubhal a tr&oacute;m ch&iacute;abh.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CIA 'ta roi Oicha gu <HI>Cathmor</HI></L>
<L>An cear-am&s;air a&s;lin fein?</L>
<L>Am bail fios duit, air &s;ri na ncruai-bheum?</L>
<L>Cia u&s;&s;a, mhic dubhra nan &s;peur?</L>
<L>Na &s;h&eacute;s u, am fionas an Ri,</L>
<L>Do chaol-thannais, on n' am o-&s;hean;</L>
<L>Na nguth u, o neoil nam fras,</L>
<L>Le cunairt <HI>Erin</HI> na ncolg &s;ean?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NI mfear &s;iubhail dubhra mi-fhein,</L>
<L>Ni nguth mi, o neol, na cruaim:</L>
<L>Ach ta m' fhocul, le cunairt na h' <HI>Erin.</HI></L>
<L>An cualas duit coppan na fuaim?</L>
<L>Ni ntais &eacute;, Ri <HI>Atha</HI> nan &s;ruth,</L>
<L>A thaomas an fhuaim air oicha.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="233" REF="263">
<L>TAOMAGH an &s;eod a ghuth fein,</L>
<L>'S fon clar&s;ich, do <HI>Chathmor</HI> an fhuaim,</L>
<L>Ta aitis, mhic dubhra nan &s;peur,</L>
<L>Lo&s;ga air m' anam, gun ghruaim.</L>
<L>Se ceoil chiean-fheona na ncruai-bheum,</L>
<L>A m' oicha, air a&s;ri' nan &s;i&auml;n,</L>
<L>Nuair la&s;as anam nan &s;&oacute;n;</L>
<L>A chl&aacute;n an cruadal do mi&auml;n.</L>
<L>Ta &s;iol-meata a nconi, na mfiamh,</L>
<L>A ngleanan na n' o&s;na tl&aacute;,</L>
<L>Far an aom ceo-maidin, ri &s;liabh,</L>
<L>O ghorm-&s;huibhal &s;ruthan na mbl&aacute;r.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NI meata, chean-uia nan &s;&oacute;n,</L>
<L>An &s;eans'ra', on thuit mi-fein,</L>
<L>Bu choni doigh dubhra nan t&oacute;n,</L>
<L>An tir fhadda &s;iol cholgach na mbeum.</L>
<L>Ach ni n&s;olas do m'anam tl&aacute;</L>
<L>Fuaim mh&aacute;l a bhais on raoin,</L>
<L>Thig e&s;&s;in nach geil gu br&aacute;th;</L>
<L>Mo&s;guil bard focuil a &s;caoin.&mdash;</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>MAR charric, 's &s;ruthan ri taobh,</L>
<L>'M fa&s;ich na mfaoin bhean,</L>
<L><PB N="234" REF="264">
Shes <HI>Cathmor,</HI> cean-feona nach maoin,&mdash;</L>
<L>An deoir&mdash;</L>
<L>Mar oitag, air anam le br&oacute;n,</L>
<L>Thanic guth caoin na h'oi,</L>
<L>Mo&s;gla cuina talamh nan bean</L>
<L>A caomh-choni aig &s;ruthan na nglean;</L>
<L>Roi n' &aacute;m an d' thanic &eacute; gu borb</L>
<L>Gu cabhar <HI>Chonmor</HI> na ncolg fiar.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>A NION coigrich nan l&aacute;n,</L>
<L>(Thionta i cean on d' &s;h&oacute;n)</L>
<L>'S fadda fa, m' &s;huil, an cruai,</L>
<L>Cran flathal <HI>Inis-uina</HI> nan t&oacute;n.</L>
<L>Ta m' anam, do thubhairt mi-fein,</L>
<L>An tru&s;can nan &s;ian cear,</L>
<L>Car &s;on a la&s;&s;a an dealra &s;o-f hein,</L>
<L>Gus am pil mi, an s&iacute;, on d' &s;hliabh?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NA ghlas m' aighai', na t' f hionas, a lamh-gheal,</L>
<L>'S tu togmhail do m' eagal an Ri?</L>
<L>'S &aacute;m cunairt, annir nan tr&oacute;m chiabh,</L>
<L>Am do m' anam, m&oacute;r-thalla na &s;ri!</L>
<L>Attas e, tomhail mar &s;ruth,</L>
<L>A taomagh air <HI>Cacl</HI> na nerua&iacute;-bheum.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="235" REF="265">
<L>AN taobh carric cho&s;ach, air <HI>Lona,</HI></L>
<L>Mo chaochan, nan &s;ruthan cr&oacute;m,</L>
<L>Glas, &aacute; nciabh na h' ao&s;e,</L>
<L>'Ta <HI>Claon-mhal,</HI> Ri clar&s;ich nam f&oacute;n.</L>
<L>O s'cion ta cran-darrach na mfuaim,</L>
<L>Agus &s;iubhal nan rua-bhoc &s;liom,</L>
<L>'Ta forum na &s;ri' na chluais</L>
<L>'S &eacute; 'g aomagh &aacute; n&s;muina nach tiom.</L>
<L>An &s;in bith do thalla, <HI>Shul-mhalla,</HI></L>
<L>Gus an il&s;ich forum na mbeum:</L>
<L>Gus &aacute;m p&iacute;l mi, an la&s;&s;a na cruai',</L>
<L>O thru&s;can dubhra na bein:</L>
<L>On che&auml;ch do thru&s;&s;as o <HI>Lona</HI></L>
<L>Ma choni mo ruin fein.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>THUIT gath-&s;oluis air anam na h'oi,</L>
<L>Las i &s;uas, fa' choir an Ri:</L>
<L>Thionta i &aacute; h' aighai ri <HI>Cathmor,</HI></L>
<L>A ciabh-bh&oacute;g ans' na h' o&s;na &aacute; &s;ri?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>REUPAR iulluir nan &s;pe&uuml;r &aacute;rd,</L>
<L>O mh&oacute;r-&s;r&uacute;th gaoith na nglean;</L>
<L>Nuair chi' &eacute; na ruai-bhuic, fa' choir,</L>
<L>Cl&aacute;n elid na m&s;aoin bhean,</L>
<L><PB N="236" REF="266">
Mu ntionta <HI>Cathmor</HI> na ncruai-bheum,</L>
<L>On d' &s;r&iacute; mu n' erich d&aacute;n.&mdash;</L>
<L>Faicim&s;e u, ghasgaich na ngeur l&aacute;n,</L>
<L>O thru&s;can an dubhra d&uacute;',</L>
<L>Nuair thogas ceo mu m' choni fein,</L>
<L>Air <HI>Lona</HI> na n' ioma &s;r&uacute;'?</L>
<L>Nuair 's fadda, o m' &s;huil, u &s;heoid!</L>
<L>Puail coppan na mfuaim &aacute;rd.</L>
<L>Pill&eacute; &s;olas, do m' anam, 's &eacute; nce&ouml;</L>
<L>'S mi aig aoma air carric liom fein.</L>
<L>Ach mo thuit u&mdash;mar ri coigrich ata m&iacute;!</L>
<L>Thigga' do ghuth o neoil,</L>
<L>Gu oi <HI>Inis-uina,</HI> 's i f&aacute;n.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>OG-GHEUG <HI>Lumoin</HI> an fheur,</L>
<L>Com dh' aoma tu, 'n&s;trachda nan &s;ian?</L>
<L>'S tric thionta <HI>Cathmor</HI> &oacute; nbhl&aacute;r</L>
<L>Du'-thaomagh air aighai' nan &s;liabh.</L>
<L>Mar mhellain, do m' fein, ta &s;leagh nan l&oacute;t,</L>
<L>'S iad prunagh air c&oacute;s nan &s;ciath;</L>
<L>Dh' erim, mo &s;holluis, on d' &s;hr&iacute;;</L>
<L>Mar thein-oicha, o thaoma nan ni&auml;l</L>
<L>Na p&iacute;l, a dheo-ghreina, on ghlean</L>
<L>Nuair dhluthichas forum na ncolg&punc;</L>
<L><PB N="237" REF="267">
Eagal teach&aacute; do nabhad o m'lamh,</L>
<L>Mar theich iad, o &s;hiean' &s;ra' na m <HI>B&oacute;lg.</HI></L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CHUALAS le <HI>Sonm&oacute;r</HI> air <HI>Cluanar,</HI></L>
<L>Thuit fa <HI>Chormac</HI> na nge&uacute;r l&aacute;n,</L>
<L>Tri lo dhorch an Ri,</L>
<L>Mu n' f hear, a gh' aom an &s;ri na glean.</L>
<L>Chuinac min-bhean, an s&oacute;n &aacute; nceo.</L>
<L>Phro&s;nich &s;ud d' i &s;iubhal gu &s;liabh,</L>
<L>Thog i bogha, fos n' io&s;al,</L>
<L>Gu dol marri laoch nan &s;ciath.</L>
<L>Do n' ainir luigh dubhra air <HI>Atha,</HI></L>
<L>Nuair &s;huilagh &aacute; ngai&s;gach gu gniomh.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>O CHEUD &s;ruthan aonach na h'oicha,</L>
<L>Thaom &s;iol <HI>Alnecma</HI> &s;ios.</L>
<L>Chualas &s;cia' cha&s;machd an Ri,</L>
<L>Mho&s;guil a n' anam gu &s;ri'</L>
<L>Bha' an &s;iubhal, a mforum nan l&aacute;n,</L>
<L>Gu <HI>Ullin,</HI> talamh na ncr&aacute;n.</L>
<L>Bhuail <HI>S&oacute;nm&oacute;r,</HI> air uari', an &s;ciath</L>
<L>Cean-feona na mborb thriath.</L>
<L>Na ndeabh, lean <HI>Sul-allin</HI></L>
<L>Air aoma na mfras,</L>
<L><PB N="238" REF="268">
Bu &s;holus &iacute;s, air aonach,</L>
<L>Nuair thaom iad air gleanta glas.</L>
<L>Ta ceamna flathail air l&oacute;m,</L>
<L>Nuair thog iad, ri aghai nan t&oacute;m.</L>
<L>B' eagal d' i &s;ealla an Ri&mdash;</L>
<L>Dh' f h&aacute;g i, 'n <HI>Atha</HI> na mfri'.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NUAIR dh' erich forum na mbeum,</L>
<L>Agus thaom iad, &s;a cheille, &s;a chath,</L>
<L>Loi&s;g <HI>Sonmor,</HI> mar theina nan &s;peur,</L>
<L>Thanic <HI>Sul-aluin</HI> na mflath.</L>
<L>A folt &s;caoilta, &s;a n' o&s;na,</L>
<L>A h'anam aig o&s;parn mon' Ri.</L>
<L>Dh' aom &eacute; an t' &s;hri' mu r&uacute;n nan laoich,</L>
<L>Theich nabhad fa' dhubhra nan &s;peur</L>
<L>Luigh <HI>Cluanar</HI> gun f huil,</L>
<L>Gun f huil, air tigh caoil gun leus.&mdash;</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NI n' d' erich fearg <HI>Shon-mhor</HI> nan l&aacute;n,</L>
<L>Bha' lo gu dorcha, 's gu m&aacute;l:</L>
<L>Ghluais <HI>Sul-allin</HI> mu gorm-&s;ru' fein,</L>
<L>A &s;uil an reachda nan deuir.</L>
<L>Bu lionmhar a &s;ealla, gu caoin</L>
<L>Air gai&s;gach &s;abhach nach faoin.</L>
<L>Ach thionta i a &s;uillin tla,</L>
<L><PB N="239" REF="269">
O &s;healla, an laoch thuatal.</L>
<L>Mho&s;gul blair, mar f horum nan nial,</L>
<L>Ghluais doran o anam m&oacute;r,</L>
<L>Chunas a ceamna, le aitis,</L>
<L>'Sa lamh-gheal air clar&s;ich na mf&oacute;n.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NA chruai a ghluais an Ri, gun dail,</L>
<L>Bhuail &eacute; 'n &s;ciath cho&s;ach &aacute;rd;</L>
<L>Gu &aacute;rd, air darach nan &s;ian,</L>
<L>Aig <HI>Lubhair</HI> na n'ioma &s;ruth.</L>
<L>Seachd coppain a bh', air an &s;c&eacute;,</L>
<L>Seachd focuil an Ri' do &s;hluagh;</L>
<L>A thaomagh air o&s;na nan &s;peur,</L>
<L>Air finach&aacute; m&oacute;r na m <HI>B&oacute;lg.</HI></L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>AIR gach copan ta re&uuml;l do n'oicha;</L>
<L><HI>Cean-mathon</HI> nan ros gun &s;cleo',</L>
<L><HI>Caol-derna,</HI> o neoil aig eri',</L>
<L><HI>Ul-oicho</HI> an tru&s;can do che&ouml;.</L>
<L>'Ta <HI>Caon-cathlin,</HI> air carric, a dealra</L>
<L><HI>Re&uuml;l-dura'</HI> ar gorm-th&oacute;n on iar:</L>
<L>Leth-chellagh &s;olus an ui&s;ce.</L>
<L>Ta <HI>Ber-thein,</HI> las-&s;huil nan &s;liabh,</L>
<L>Sealla &s;ios, o choille &s;a n'aonach;</L>
<L><PB N="240" REF="270">
Air m&aacute;l &s;hi&umacr;bhal, s&eacute;lgair 's &eacute; tri&auml;l,</L>
<L>Roi ghleanan, an dubhra bhraonach,</L>
<L>Le faogh rua-bhuic nan leum &aacute;rd.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>TOMHAIL, a mi&auml;n na &s;c&eacute;,</L>
<L>'Ta la&s;&s;a <HI>Ton-theina,</HI> gun neoil,</L>
<L>An rinnac a &s;heal, roi n'oicha,</L>
<L>Air <HI>Lear-thon</HI> a chuain mhoir;</L>
<L><HI>Lear-thon,</HI> cean-feona na m <HI>Bolg</HI></L>
<L>A nceud-f hear a &s;huibhail air gaoith.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>LEATHAIN &s;caoile &s;eoil bh&aacute;n an Ri.</L>
<L>Gu <HI>Inis-fail</HI> nan ioma &s;ru?</L>
<L>Thaom oicha air aighai' a chuain,</L>
<L>Agus ce&auml;ch nan tru&s;can du'.</L>
<L>Bha' gaoith a caochla dlu' &s;a n&s;peur.</L>
<L>Leum loingheas, o th&ograve;n gu t&oacute;n;</L>
<L>Nuair dh' erich <HI>Ton-theina</HI> nan &s;tuagh</L>
<L>Caon-&s;healla, o bhri&s;ta' nan nial,</L>
<L>B' aitis do <HI>Learthon</HI> tein-uil na mbuaigh,</L>
<L>A dealra air domhan nan &s;ian.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>FA' &s;leagh <HI>Chathmor</HI> na ncolg &s;ean.</L>
<L>Dhui&s;ge an guth, a dhui&s;ga Baird.</L>
<L><PB N="241" REF="271">
Thaom iad du', o thaobh nan &s;liabh,</L>
<L>Le clar&s;ich ghrin 's gach lamh.</L>
<L>Le aitis m&oacute;r, &s;h&eacute;s rompa an Ri,</L>
<L>Mar f hear-&s;iubhal, ri teas la 'nglean.</L>
<L>Nuair chluinas &eacute;, fadda &s;a nr&eacute;th,</L>
<L>Caoin thorman &s;ruthan na mbean:</L>
<L>Sruthan a bhri&s;tas &s;a n' f ha&s;ich,</L>
<L>O charric thaobh-ghlas nan rua-bhoc.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CUR &s;on chluinim guth ard an Ri&mdash;</L>
<L>N' &aacute;m codal, a n'oicha nan fras?</L>
<L>Am facas tanais nach beo,</L>
<L>Mea&s;c t'a&s;lin aig aoma glas?</L>
<L>Air neoil am bail an aitach fuar,</L>
<L>Feaghai' f&oacute;n <HI>Fhonair</HI> na mfleagh?</L>
<L>'S lionmhar an &s;iubhal air r&eacute;th,</L>
<L>Far an tog an &s;iol an t' &s;hleagh.</L>
<L>Na n' erich, ar cronan air th&uacute;s,</L>
<L>Mu n' fhear, nach tog on t' &s;hlea' gu brath;</L>
<L>Fear cho&s;cairt, air glean nan &s;loigh,</L>
<L>O <HI>Mhoma</HI> nan ioma bad?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NI dith-chuin do m'dorcha na mbl&aacute;r</L>
<L>Chiean-fheona na mbard, o th&uacute;s,</L>
<L><PB N="242" REF="272">
Togar cloch do aig <HI>Lubhair</HI> na nc&aacute;rn,</L>
<L>Ait-coni dh' <HI>Fholdath</HI> '&s;do chliu.</L>
<L>Ach taom m' anam, air &aacute;m nan laoich,</L>
<L>Air na bliaghna', &s;o n d' erich iad &s;uas,</L>
<L>Air t&oacute;n <HI>Inis-uina</HI> na ncolg.</L>
<L>Ni n' aitis, do <HI>Chathmor</HI> a bhain,</L>
<L>Cuina <HI>Lumon</HI> inis uina na n&s;loi?</L>
<L><HI>Lumon</HI> talamh na n&s;ruth,</L>
<L>Caon-choni na mb&aacute;n-bhroilach Oi.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>LUMON na &s;ruth!</L>
<L>'Ta u dealra, air m' anam fein,</L>
<L>'Ta do ghrian, air do thaobh,</L>
<L>Air carric na ncr&aacute;n bu tr&oacute;m.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>TAT' elid chear</L>
<L>Do dhearg bar-mhor, a mea&s;c na mbad</L>
<L>A faicin air &s;liabh.</L>
<L>An colg-chu, a &s;iubhal grad.</L>
<L>M&agrave;l air an r&eacute;th</L>
<L>Ta ceamna nan Oi:</L>
<L>Oi lamh-gheal nan teud</L>
<L>'S na bogha cr&oacute;m, &s;a mhoi;</L>
<L><PB N="243" REF="273">
Togmhail an gorm-&s;huil tl&agrave;,</L>
<L>On leatain bhar-bhui, air &s;liabh na mflath.</L>
<L>Ni bail ceamna <HI>Lear-thon</HI> &s;a bhein,</L>
<L>Cean <HI>Inis</HI> na ngeug <HI>uina.</HI></L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>TA &ecirc; togmhail du-dharach air t&oacute;n,</L>
<L>A ncamis <HI>Chluba,</HI> nan ioma &s;tua',</L>
<L>An du-dharach, bhuain &eacute; o <HI>Lumon,</HI></L>
<L>Gu &s;iubhal air aighai a chuain.</L>
<L>Thionta Oi an &s;uillin tl&aacute;,</L>
<L>On Ri, mo ntuitagh &eacute; &s;ios.</L>
<L>Ni mfacas le&ouml; riamh an long,</L>
<L>Cear mharcach a chuain mhoir.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>GHLAOI' anois, an Ri a ghaoith.</L>
<L>Mea&s;c ce&oacute; na marra glais.</L>
<L>Dh' erich <HI>Inis-fail</HI> gu gorm:</L>
<L>Thuit, gu dian, oicha na mfrais.</L>
<L>Bhuail eagal <HI>Clan-Bholga</HI> gu lua'</L>
<L>Ghlan neoil, o <HI>Thon-theina</HI> nan &s;tua'</L>
<L>A ncamis <HI>Chulbin</HI> dh' atich an long</L>
<L>Far am fregra' coille do th&oacute;n.</L>
<L>Bu chopach an &s;in an &s;ru'</L>
<L><PB N="244" REF="274">
O charric <HI>Duth-umha</HI> na nc&oacute;s,</L>
<L>'San dealra tannais nach beo</L>
<L>Le ncruith caochlach fein.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>THANIC a&s;lin gu <HI>Lear-thon</HI> nan long,</L>
<L>Seachd Samla do nlina nach beo,</L>
<L>Ch&ubreve;alas a nguth bri&s;ta, tr&oacute;m:</L>
<L>Chunas an &s;iol an ce&ouml;.</L>
<L>Chunas &s;iol <HI>Atha</HI> na ncolg&mdash;</L>
<L>'San cl&aacute;n ciean-uia' na m <HI>Bolg.</HI></L>
<L>Thaom iad a mfeachda' fein,</L>
<L>Mar cheach a terna on bhein,</L>
<L>Nuair &s;hiubhlas &eacute; glas, fa' o&s;na,</L>
<L>Air <HI>Atha</HI> nan ioma dos.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>THOG <HI>Lear-thon</HI> talla <HI>Shamla,</HI></L>
<L>Ri caoin fh&oacute;n clar&s;ich nan teud.</L>
<L>Dh' aom eilid <HI>Erin,</HI> o cheamna</L>
<L>Aig ai&s;ra' glas nan &s;ruth.</L>
<L>Nin dith-chuin do <HI>Lumon</HI> uina,</L>
<L>Na <HI>Flathal,</HI> gheal-lamhach na mbua'gh</L>
<L>'S &iacute; comhaid, air marcach nan t&oacute;n</L>
<L>O Thulach nan eilid ruagh.</L>
<L><PB N="245" REF="275">
LUMON na &s;ruth</L>
<L>Ta &uacute; dealra' air m' anam fein!</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>MHOSGUIL gath &s;oluis on ear,</L>
<L>Dh' erich &aacute;rd-chiean che&auml;ich na bein.</L>
<L>Chunas air cladach na ngleanan</L>
<L>A ncr&oacute;m chaochan ghlas-&s;ruthach fein.</L>
<L>Chualas &s;ciath <HI>Chathmor</HI> na ncolg,</L>
<L>Mho&s;guil &s;iol <HI>Erin</HI> na m <HI>Bolg.</HI></L>
<L>Mar mhuir dhomhail, nuair ghlui&s;as gu geur</L>
<L>Fuaim aitti, air aghai' nan &s;peur:</L>
<L>Taoma tuin, o thaobh gu taobh,</L>
<L>Aig aomagh a nglas chiean bao;</L>
<L>Gun eolas, air &s;iubhal a chuain.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>TROM is m&aacute;l, gu <HI>Lon</HI> na &s;ruth</L>
<L>Ghluais <HI>Suil-mhalla</HI> nan ro&s;c tl&aacute;;</L>
<L>Ghluais as thionta n' Oi le br&oacute;n:</L>
<L>A gorm-&s;huil fa &s;hilla bl&aacute;.</L>
<L>Nuair thanic i gu carric chruai'</L>
<L>Du chromagh air gleanan an <HI>L&oacute;n</HI></L>
<L><PB N="246" REF="276">
Sheal i, o bri&s;tagh a ceil,</L>
<L>Air Ri <HI>Atha</HI>&mdash;dh' aom i &s;ios.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>PUAIL teud, a mhic Alpain na mf&oacute;n,</L>
<L>Ambail &s;olas a nclar&s;ich na nie&ouml;l?</L>
<L>Taom air <HI>O&s;&s;ian,</HI> agus O&s;&s;un gu tr&oacute;m,</L>
<L>Ta anam a &s;namh a nce&ouml;.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>CHUALAS u, Bhaird, a m' oicha</L>
<L>Ach &s;iubhla f&oacute;n edrom uam fein!</L>
<L>'S aitis caoin thurra do dh' <HI>O&s;&s;ian</HI></L>
<L>A mbliaghna chear na h' aoi&s;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>DHREUN uaina thulloch nan tais</L>
<L>A thaomas do chean air gaoith oicha,</L>
<L>Ni bail t' f horum na mchluais fein:</L>
<L>Na faital tannais, na d' gheug ghlais.</L>
<L>'S lionmhar ceamna na marbh bu treun</L>
<L>Air o&s;na, dubh-ai&s;ra' na bein,</L>
<L>Nuair ghlui&s;as a ghellach, an ear,</L>
<L>Mar ghlas-&s;cia, du &s;hiubhal nan &s;peur.</L>
<L>ULLIN, a Charril, a Raono</L>
<L>Guith am&s;air a dh' aom o-&s;hean:</L>
<L><PB N="247" REF="277">
Cluinim &s;iobh an dorchadas <HI>Shelma</HI></L>
<L>Agus mo&s;glibh&s;e anam nan d&aacute;n!</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>NI ncluinim &s;iobh &s;hiol na mf&oacute;n,</L>
<L>Cia an talla do neoil, 'mbail ar &s;uain</L>
<L>Na tribuail &s;iobh, clar&s;ach nach tr&oacute;m,</L>
<L>An tru&s;can ceo-madin 's cruaim.</L>
<L>Far an erich, gu fuaimar a ghrian</L>
<L>O &s;tuaigh na ncean glas?</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>FINIS.</TRAILER>
